The paper also proposes a new loss function, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on several datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of loss functions, which falls under the category of cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
